      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Hoffman Machinery was a company in Syracuse, New York, a manufacturer of "Sanitary Steam Knit Goods Presses" for the textile industry.  W. B. Harden was their advertising manager. [<emph render="italic">American Wool and Cotton Reporter</emph>, Nov. 10, 1921, p. 104.]  The Syracuse Triplex Presser Company produced garment presses and as of 1922 was "a comparatively new company." [<emph render="italic">Textile World</emph>, September 16, 1922, p. 37]  Harden's connection with this company is unknown.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">W. B. Harden Scrapbook</emph> consists of a large album containing advertising literature and correspondence pertaining to the Hoffman Machinery Company and the Syracuse Triplex Presser Company.  Both companies manufactured garment presses and/or fabric presses for the textile and garment industry.  A substantial amount of additional material is laid in.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
